postcontent: This is a fine example of an all original Savage model 99 TakeDown Rifle in .303 Savage caliber, Manufactured in 1930. Aurther Savage developed this rifle in the 1890's and it has continued to be one of the finest rifles for North American hunting for over 100 years. This rifle is mechanically perfect with a brite and shiney bore. It sports it's original Marbles front & rear tang peep sights. The barrell retains about 80% of the original bluing, without any pitting. The receiver shows a littlemore wear and patina as is usual with the model 99. Color case hardening is still visable on the lever with a little bit of the original protective varnish. This handy takedown rifle has a straight grip stock which is cracked at the receiver and a Slim Schnable fore end with the originalserial number stamped inside. The stock appears to have been chipped and reformed at the butt as evidenced by the metal buttplate overhang.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage 99 .308 win
postcontent:
I'm selling my old Savage model 99 lever action .308 rifle. The rifle is in amazing shape aside for a very minor amount of bluing wear around the muzzle. Other than that the bore is bright and shiny and you can still see the jeweling on the bolt and the case hardening on the lever. This rifle has the brass round counter. Rifle comes with a tasco 3x9 with factory side flip rings and a padded hard case (everything in the picture). 

This rifle is already a collector's item but it has a cool connection to Vermont. This is the same model and caliber rifle that used by James Bond in Ian Flemming's For Your Eyes Only. Bond uses it on a personal revenge mission for M to kill a group of gangsters responsible for the death of M's close friends. Bond enters the U.S. through Frelighsburg Canada under cover of darkness travels past Lake Carmi and eventually exercises his license to kill at Echo Lake; where the gangsters are hiding out.
